      • getPartToModify

        public void getPartToModify​(Part selectedPart)
        This method get the data from the part selected to modify. This method sets the data in the text fields on this page to the part selected from the Parts Table on the Main Screen. This method also assess if the chosen part is In-House or Outsourced and change the label for that text field accordingly. RUNTIME ERROR - When attempting to access this form via the Modify button on the Main Screen, it produced a Null Pointer Exception. The exception pointed to the partID when debugged. I had not set the partID to the text field in the FXML for this form. Once the fxid was set, the problem was fixed.
        Parameters:
        selectedPart - - this variable is used to hold the data from the part selected from the Parts Table.

      • onSaveModify

        public void onSaveModify​(javafx.event.ActionEvent actionEvent)
        This is the method for the Save button. This method first check that the data entered into the Inventory, Min, and Max fields meet the required specifications. This method then saves the modified part data to the Parts Table on the Main Screen. If the In-House radio button is selected the Machine ID is saved. If the Outsourced radio button is selected, the Company Name is saved.
        Parameters:
        actionEvent - - this method is executed when the Save button is selected on this pane.
